{"error":0,"message":"","data":[{"show_ID":"2249","airdate":"1613070000","name_switch":"off","DJ":"ziona and Slaygon","showname":"Hello there, Valentine!","blurb":"Hi Folks,\n\nNot that we care so much, but there is a thing coming up that is called Valentine's day by Earthlings. Want to show off your favourite C64 or Amiga related love songs? Maybe this is your time to shine then! =)\n\nWe don't take it very seriously, so chill, this is not a requirement for requests, but inserting a few of those could be fun, we think!\n\nJoin us with all your ears and fingers for chatting!","nice_showname":"<strong><big>ziona and Slaygon<\/big><\/strong><br \/>Hello there, Valentine!","nice_airdate":"Thursday 11th February, 2021<br \/>at 20:00 USRT"},{"show_ID":"2251","airdate":"1613847600","name_switch":"off","DJ":"Remix64.com","showname":"Remixer of the Year Awards 2020","blurb":"The time has come to celebrate and acknowledge the remixers' work in the C64 and Amiga community by presenting the yearly ROTY Awards, as voted by the users at www.remix64.com.\n\nThis year it's SLAY Radio's turn to give out the awards and give you a run-down of what happened in 2020.\n\n2020 was one of the most active years in recent memory, with 174 c64 remixes, 48 Amiga remixes and a whopping 194 tracks over 11 albums, giving us a grand total of 416 tracks to enjoy!\n\nSo, join us as we go through some highlights of 2020 and announce the runner-ups and winners of each category!","nice_showname":"<strong><big>Remix64.com<\/big><\/strong><br \/>Remixer of the Year Awards 2020","nice_airdate":"Saturday 20th February, 2021<br \/>at 20:00 USRT"}]}